ZH: 请问你有车票吗？
EN: Do you have a train ticket?

ZH: 我需要买一张去北京的机票。
EN: I need to buy a plane ticket to Beijing.

ZH: 这是您的入场票。
EN: This is your entrance ticket.

ZH: 我从来没有丢过飞机票。
EN: I have never lost a plane ticket.

ZH: 买票的时候要记得确认时间。
EN: Remember to confirm the time when buying tickets.

ZH: 他的车票已经过期了。
EN: His train ticket has expired.

ZH: 票务处在哪里？
EN: Where is the ticket office?

ZH: 你可以用信用卡购买门票。
EN: You can purchase tickets with a credit card.

ZH: 我们应该提前预订票。
EN: We should book tickets in advance.

ZH: 不要在门口买假票。
EN: Do not buy fake tickets at the gate.

ZH: 你的票被吸入了机器。
EN: Your ticket got sucked into the machine.

ZH: 我收到了体育赛事门票。
EN: I received tickets for the sports event.

ZH: 她泪流满面，因为她没有买到票。
EN: She was in tears because she didn't get tickets.

ZH: 票已经售完了。
EN: Tickets are sold out.

ZH: 我们必须提前预订门票。
EN: We must book tickets in advance.

ZH: 请务必保管好您的演出票。
EN: Please keep your show ticket safe.

ZH: 我在火车站买了一张单程车票。
EN: I bought a one-way train ticket at the station.

ZH: 稍后请出示您的购票凭证。
EN: Please show your ticket confirmation later.

ZH: 由于突发情况，我们的演出取消了，请保留您的门票以换取下次演出的入场券。
EN: Due to unexpected circumstances, our performance has been cancelled, please keep your tickets for entry to the next show.

ZH: 你可以使用手机应用程序购买护照。
EN: You can purchase your passport using your mobile application.
